Silvercrest also made cheap burgers for Burger King, which, to date, insists there is no evidence that its products were contaminated.

One British company, Dalepak, which is also owned by ABP foods, produced burgers contaminated with horse DNA for Iceland from a factory in Yorkshire.

Dalepak also makes cheap burgers for Waitrose, which denies that any of its products are tainted.

The management of Silvercrest are being blamed for the contamination scandal after they decided to use a series of non-approved ingredients.

These included large and cheap consignments of frozen blocks of meat off-cuts, including horse, imported from Poland.

